    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-08-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-08-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="323"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d323">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Adee</persName> to <persName
                            type="to">Baron Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-08-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 21, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 143.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to state that I am
                    advised by a telegram from the governor of Louisiana that on his return to the
                    capital he found report from the judge and district attorney in regard to the
                    lynching of the Italians at Hahnville. The governor promises to forward the
                    information by mail to-day.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Alvey A. Adee</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
